item.title: Virus fast-tracks Wesley’s retirement
item.description: Two-time NBL champion Tai Wesley has announced his retirement after deciding to put his family before basketball following a stellar career.

item.title: Driver crashes into pub fence
item.description: A woman has been charged with high-range drink-driving after allegedly crashing into a fence at the Belrose Hotel in Sydney’s north.

item.title: Virus tower fury over food donations
item.description: Fed-up residents inside one of Melbourne’s quarantined commission towers have clashed with police after they were denied access to food donation drop-offs on Monday night.

item.title: Victoria could face ‘further restrictions’
item.description: Health Minister Greg Hunt is not ruling out further restrictions being imposed in Victoria as the army prepares to lock down the border with NSW.

item.title: Man bolts from last Melbourne train
item.description: Police have ushered a man out of Sydney’s Central station after he bolted out of the last inbound train from Melbourne.

item.title: Supermarkets scrap buying limits
item.description: Coles and Woolworths are scrapping buying restrictions just weeks after reintroducing them.

item.title: Lockdown risk for 10th Melbourne tower
item.description: A 10th Melbourne public housing tower is at risk of being locked down after an infected worker reportedly visited a building in Richmond.

item.title: Who is eligible for border permit
item.description: From 11.59pm on Tuesday, only those with a permit will be able to cross the NSW-Victorian border under a harsh new lockdown designed to keep Melbourne’s spiking COVID cases out of NSW.

item.title: Children approached at shopping centre
item.description: A man accused of approaching two young girls in a shopping centre in Sydney’s eastern suburbs last week will front court today.

item.title: Landmark trial begins in Victoria
item.description: Two accused “crop sitters” have pleaded not guilty to cultivating a large commercial quantity of cannabis as Victoria’s first judge-only trial began on Monday.
